Title: Privilege Escalation: Low Privilege User Can View All Employer Data
Description: A low privilege user is able to access sensitive employer data, which is meant to be restricted to Super Admins. By exploiting a vulnerability in the access control mechanism, the low privilege user can view data that should be inaccessible to them, such as personal or business details of all employers in the system. This improper privilege enforcement leads to a serious confidentiality breach.

Impact:

Sensitive employer data, intended for Super Admin access, is exposed to lower privilege users.
This could result in unauthorized data disclosure, privacy violations, and potential misuse of the information.
Recommendation:

Enforce strict access control on sensitive data to ensure only authorized users (Super Admins) can access it.
Implement proper role-based access control (RBAC) checks on all data endpoints.
Regularly review access permissions to ensure that lower privilege users cannot access data beyond their authorization level.
